p: \b\pn. I'm so glad you decided to show up.
\bEvery time I've failed, you were there to see it.
\bAfter we tried to create the perfect Delta Pokemon...
\bAfter we experimented with Mega Evolution, and the incident with Pokerus...
\bAnd now that our experiment with armor failed too, you might think we're running out of ideas.
\bTell me, \pn, Nora.\nDo you know the myth of the Unovan dragon?
\bLegend speaks of a gargantuan dragon that once reigned over all of Unova.
\bIts power was supervised by two brothers- the princes of the region.
\bHowever, these brothers constantly fought over their beliefs.
\bOne seeked truth, one strove for ideals, and- finding no middle ground- they split the great dragon into three.
\bReshiram- truth- and Zekrom- ideals- emerged, where Kyurem was left as the Dragon's empty husk.
\bWhile the Dragon did rule in Unova, the war between the brothers was in Torren.\nIn fact, the great splitting was at this very spot.
\bA shrine was built here in the hopes that one day, the Dragon might be formed once again and bring peace to the land.
\bWhile Reukra has been busy, the most important job in the Perfection Cult was left to me.
\bIt was difficult- I needed three different legendary Pokemon- but I succeeded.
\bThe Original Dragon was said to be a sign of leadership, of wholeness.
\bIt represented opposing beliefs finding neutral ground and working together.
\bOnce we summon this creature, we'll be unstoppable.
\bThe only thing left is to begin.
\bIt's time to return to your origins!
\bJoin together, and become whole once more!
\bAnd now, great dragon of Unova!\nThe divine, perfect god!\nEmerge... ...the great Namehere!
\rAre you reading that off a scroll?
\rI'm pretty sure you're reading that wrong.
\rI think you're supposed to say the Dragon's name at that part, not just "Namehere".
\bOh. Huh. That's what the parentheses are for.
\bNobody knows the name of the original dragon!
\bThe only names that survived were Reshiram, Zekrom, and Kyurem...
\bHow are we supposed to bring it back, then?
\bFine. I was hoping to resurrect the Original Dragon today, but it seems like that's not happening.
\bI'll find that name.\nI'll search every scroll, text, or book until I learn it.
\bI split you into Kyurem-White and Zekrom! Come forth and serve me!
\bI'll deal with the two of you here and now!
\bI wasn't done yet! Get back together!
\bI'm so glad you're okay! You're not hurt, are you?
\bYou better hold on tight to your friend, because once I find that name...
\bOh man, I'm getting excited just thinking about my revenge!
\bI'm glad nobody knows, but I can't help wondering...
\rWell, I have a theory. It's probably wrong, but...
\rKyurem is the shell of the original dragon, right?\nIt's what was left after Reshiram and Zekrom split from it.
\rAnd there's the fact that the fusions are called Kyurem-White and Kyurem-Black...
\rWell, I don't know if you remember this, but back at the Utira Library, I was looking at a book on Unovan word structures.
\rThere was a page that talked about the legendary trio.
\rReshi- was a prefix that meant truth, Zek- was a prefix that meant ideals.
\rNobody really agrees on what Kyu- means, but most translations believe it's "whole" or "complete".
\rI never really questioned how little sense that made.\nKyurem is the opposite of complete, after all.
\rTaen said that the original dragon was perfect- a symbol of different beliefs working together.
\r...maybe a more accurate translation of Kyu- would be "perfect".
\r\pn... the Infernal Cult said they were in the mountains, right?
\rWe have to go after them.\nIf we strike them before they strike us, maybe we can have a chance.
\rYour Mew can transform into anything it has the DNA of, right?
\rThat's how you used Shaymin's ability to get around, even though you didn't actually have it.
\rWhy don't you take this? It's a hair from Celebi's head.
Obtained the \rCelebi DNA\c[0].\nMew can now use Celebi's DNA to transform and use the Tesseract ability outside of battle.
\rTo use Tesseract, you need to find glowing areas where spacetime is torn.
If it's \c[7]white\c[0], you can travel back in time, but if it's \rred\c[0], you can move other objects through time.
\rYou're smart, I'm sure you'll figure it out.
\rIt's a lot less complicated than it sounds. Just make sure you're close to the rip!

\bIf you need anything, like to train or something, just let me know, OK?
\bI'd be glad to give you a hand.

\bFor helping me out... and Reshiram, too.
\bIf you need anything, like to train or something, just let me know, OK?
\bI'd be glad to give you a hand.
\bI have one of the most powerful Pokemon ever .
\bYou have a few little...\n...I don't even know what you have.
\b\pn, Orion. I'm so glad that at least someone competent came to see my victory.
\bI've worked as hard as I can to get the strongest possible Pokemon.
\bNow, Mewtwo, Zekrom, Reshiram, and Kyurem are mine.
\bI have the name of the Original Dragon this time.
\bI can't believe it was just Kyurem. I never thought it could be that simple.
\bWhy would it be any different? We call its other formes Kyurem-B and Kyurem-W.
\bIf Kyurem was the remnant that connected Reshiram to Zekrom, it only makes sense that it would have the dragon's name.
\bI can't believe I'm so close. The sheer power of the Original Dragon is almost in my grasp.
\bAnd your little green slugs can't stop me.
\bI call upon you, great titan of the Unova Region!
\rI just... I just need to know...
\rWhy do you want to live this kind of life?
\b...that is the worst attempt at stalling I've ever seen.
\bDo you really think I'm going to fall for that?
\bYou can't fool me that easily- I'm not going to start monologuing.
\rThen I'll stall you by force. Bring it on!
\bA battle? Fine. I'll take both of you on, easily.\nI've missed double battles.
\bPlus, I've got a new trick from a far away region I've been meaning to test out.
\bEven my new Crystal gimmick didn't work out...
\bI went all the way to Kuria for that junk. What a letdown.
\bI assume you have some backup plan? What were you stalling me for?
\rGet ready, turdstain, because you're about to see something amazing.
\rCome on out! Let's show him what we're made of!
\bOh, it's Zygarde. You had me worried for a second.
\bZygarde doesn't have a chance against me.\nNot against the combined power of Mewtwo and my dragon.
\bNot bad, but your legendary can't save you now.
\bMine are far more powerful than yours.
\rThat's what Reukra realized and you didn't.
\rIt's not all about being the strongest or the smartest.
\rIt's about teamwork. People and Pokemon working in harmony.
\bRiiiiight, let me know how that works out for you.
\bKyurem, the all-powerful Original Dragon, emerge! Show me your power!
\rLike I said... it's all about teamwork.
\rZygarde isn't just one Pokemon, it's a network. A hivemind of tiny cells all working in harmony.
\rAnd when all of those cells decide to fight alongside each other...
\rWe get to see Zygarde's Complete Forme.
\rA bit of an ironic name, isn't it?
\rZygarde is the guardian of the ecosystem. Its job is to stop huge nature-destroying events like this.
\rIt was easy to stop your summoning.
\rZygarde's Complete Forme is perfect. Not only will it stop your plans... but it'll beat you and your Pokemon so thoroughly you'll never be able to try it again.
\bZekrom, fight back! What are you doing?
\bGail, that's my friend! Call Zygarde off!
\rIt's too late, Orion. I'm sorry.\nThis is for the good of the region.
\bNo.. there has to be another way...
\b\pn, please, do something. You gotta help. You promised!
\bI can't... I can't live without my friend.

\rOh there you are, \pn. I've been looking for you!
\rSo I kind of forgot to give you something important... Something that you've probably been waiting to get your hands on for over a year? Or maybe it just feels that
\rIt'll be useful for unleashing the full potential of Zygarde.\nHere you go!
\rWeird name, right? Strangest "cube" I've ever seen.\nThat there's an artifact that was first discovered in Kalos and later researched in the Alola region which is
used to store the fragments of Zygarde, which are categorized as Cells or Cores.\nYou're gonna want to store as much of them in the Zygarde Cube as possible if
you ever want to bring out that Megazord-looking form that you faced off against earlier.
\rI bet you'd like to be able to just use its big boss form whenever you'd like, huh?\nYeah, I know that feeling. But unfortunately if Zygarde was in its Complete
Forme ALL the time while traveling around with you then it wouldn't be able to act as the one who nullifies threats to the world's ecosystems.
\rSee, while Zygarde is having fun adventuring with you, another fragment of itself is on neighborhood watch duty at all times back in some boring old cave in the
Kalos region.\nThat fragment is the one that decides how much of itself it needs to gather at once in order to deal with threats like that blockhead Taen.\nSo while
Zygarde definitely doesn't mind lending you its full strength every once in a while, it can't really just go around leaving the ecosystem unprotected.
\rAnd so that brings us to the purpose of those cute little slime buddies that were all over the place during Operation Z.\nAt all times, Zygarde keeps track of things
that are happening by splitting itself into those cells and scattering them all over the world. Don't ask me how many of them there are because even if I knew where
all of them were, there's no way I'd be able to count up all of the little critters myself.
\rBut on that note, since this region is finally seeing the first real peace since well before I was even born, I'd reckon that there's less of a need for Zygarde to
spread itself out within the areas that you're watching over.\nSo there really shouldn't be any harm in scooping up some Zygarde Cells while you're running around
if you want to reconfigure the fragment of Zygarde that's in your possession.
\rIf you want Zygarde to learn any moves that it doesn't normally get by level up, then keep your eyes open for Zygarde Cores, which you can identify by the
pinkish glow that they give off while they're off wiggling around.\nBesides those 5 cores, you'll also need 45 Zygarde Cells to give your Zygarde fragment the
ability to call upon its cells for assistance when it's weakened.\nThey should all show themselves to you if you have both the Zygarde Cube and Zygarde itself on
\rThis region doesn't have anything resembling a Reassembly Unit just sitting around, so you'll need to seek out Zygarde's main fragment if you want to do any kind
of reconfiguration.\nUh, I don't really know how or when you'd manage to travel over to the Kalos region to do that though. Knowing how awesome your family is I
kind of just assumed that you'd have a way to do it.
\rAnd... actually, I think that's it. Boy, that was a lot to take in all at once, huh?\nI'm not sure if we'll meet again after this; Zygarde may have lent a fragment of itself
to you but my relationship with it hasn't changed one bit.\nI just wanted to make sure that you weren't left in the dark about all of this before I headed off to help
other regions that are in trouble.
\rOh and of course I wanted to wish you good luck and once again thank you for helping out with the near-Armageddon that bonehead almost unleashed.\nI think
that this region should be peaceful again for a loooong time, but you'll still have your work cut out for you as Augur.
\bI'm the Dragon Tutor. I know several very useful moves to teach.
\bWhat move shall I teach, then?\ch[2,5,Draco Meteor,Dual Chop,Outrage,Twister,(Cancel)]
\rOh, a shame. Maybe another time, then.
The Zygarde Cell was sucked into the Zygarde Cube!
